dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.pncmapping

Interface IPncMapping

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity

    public interface IPncMapping
extends IEntity
    IPncMapping: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    !RESTRICT_TO_STANDARD:CP! Describes a mapping between one or several Virtual Function Clusters onto Partial Network Clusters. A Virtual Function Cluster is realized by a PortGroup. A Partial Network Cluster is realized by one or more IPduGroups. !END_RESTRICT_TO_STANDARD! !RESTRICT_TO_STANDARD:AP! Describes a mapping between one or several Virtual Function Clusters onto Partial Network Clusters. A Virtual Function Cluster is realized by a PortGroup. A Partial Network Cluster is realized by one or more ServiceInstances. !END_RESTRICT_TO_STANDARD!

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

      • getPncWakeupEnable

        boolean getPncWakeupEnable()
        Query the value of the attribute PncWakeupEnable.

        If this parameter is available and set to true then this PNC will be woken up as soon as a channel wakeup occurs on a channel where this PNC is assigned to. This is ensured by adding this PNC to the corresponding channel wakeup sources during upstream mapping.
